<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARGERS CUT STRONG SAFETY MILLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON PATTERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers cut strong safety Pat Miller Sunday, leaving 11 players to cut by 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Miller played one game at linebacker for the Chargers during the 1987 strike 
and was released. He returned to make the team as a safety last year, playing 
eight games before a knee injury ended his season. 
</P>
<P>
"He doesn't figure in the top eight guys right now," Charger Coach Dan Henning 
said. "We think it's right to let him go now so he can possibly get hooked up 
and get some chances elsewhere." DON PATTERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
