<P>
FORMER CHIEF OF ITALIAN RAILWAY SYSTEM SLAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gunmen killed the former head of Italian railways in a Mafia-style ambush 
Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Ludovico Ligato was hit by about 20 bullets when three men opened 
fire as he and his wife stood outside their villa after saying goodby to dinner 
guests. 
</P>
<P>
Ligato, who resigned last year along with the entire board of Italy's railway 
system over a corruption scandal, tried to run back into the house. But the 
gunmen closed in and shot him at point-blank range. 
