NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Football League has refused reinstatement this season for Mossy 
Cade, the former Green Bay Packers' defensive back who served 15 months in 
prison for second-degree sexual assault. 
</P>
<P>
The NFL's decision was made several months ago but not announced, the Milwaukee 
Journal reported. 
</P>
<P>
Cade was paroled from prison Oct. 21, 1988. He tried unsuccessfully to play 
last year after his release. 
</P>
<P>
Cade's attorney, Randy Rueckert, said he and Cade had hoped a new commissioner 
would be in place by training camp this year. 
</P>
<P>
"It's my impression that as long as Pete Rozelle is commissioner he (Cade) is 
not going to be able to play in the NFL," Rueckert said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
