</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soccer fans wrecked the restaurant car and passenger compartments of a train 
and forced it to stop several times as it crossed East Germany to West Berlin, 
the East German news agency ADN reported. 
</P>
<P>
West Berlin police confirmed the report of damage aboard the train Saturday 
night and said they took the names of 38 fans of East Berlin's second division 
soccer club, Hertha. 
</P>
<P>
They said the fans boarded the train in the West German city of Hanover, which 
Hertha defeated, 2-0, in a league match. 
</P>
<P>
The East German news agency reported that fans destroyed "a restaurant car and 
several compartments of passenger carriages and molested railway personnel and 
other passengers." 
</P>
