<P>
S. AFRICA BLACK PUPILS TEAR-GASSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, South Africa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South African police tear-gassed hundreds of black pupils today after a protest 
march against racially segregated schools, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
They said pupils and teachers marched toward a prestigious whites-only school 
in Queenstown, near the Indian Ocean city of East London, as part of a 
nationwide defiance campaign against Pretoria's race laws. Police stopped the 
march but allowed a small delegation into the school. Tear gas was fired as 
marchers dispersed. 
</P>
<P>
In Pretoria, blacks trying to board whites-only buses today were foiled when 
drivers closed automatic doors or refused to stop. Organizers said only two 
non-white passengers, both ethnic Indians, managed to board. Witnesses said 
police arrested three blacks who attempted to board a whites-only bus in the 
center of Pretoria. 
</P>
